Text: The capital of France is Paris.
A quantum computer works by leveraging phenomena in quantum mechanics like superposition and entanglement.
The meaning of life is subjective and can differ from person to person. It can be happiness, love, contribution, or something else entirely.
The highest mountain in the world is Mount Everest.
The novel '1984' was written by George Orwell.
The boiling point of water at sea level is approximately 100 degrees Celsius or 212 degrees Fahrenheit.
The fastest land animal is the cheetah.
The average distance between Earth and the Moon is about 238,855 miles.
The chemical formula for water is H2O.
